1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:02,584
They used to bring us rice and broth

2
00:00:03,542 --> 00:00:04,834
At noon and at sunset

3
00:00:06,083 --> 00:00:12,209
In the morning they brought us cheese, <i>samoon</i> [bread roll], and tea

4
00:00:13,918 --> 00:00:18,417
Because my detention was in the first year of ISIS’s presence

5
00:00:19,500 --> 00:00:21,876
The heavy siege hadn’t happened yet

6
00:00:22,459 --> 00:00:25,918
And supplies were available during my detention

7
00:00:27,876 --> 00:00:31,626
Meaning I wasn’t imprisoned during the liberation period

8
00:00:31,918 --> 00:00:34,292
At the time of food and drink shortages

9
00:00:34,375 --> 00:00:36,792
No, I was imprisoned in the first year of ISIS

10
00:00:37,667 --> 00:00:40,709
I was imprisoned in the first year of their entry

11
00:00:41,167 --> 00:00:43,417
There was food, they brought us rice and broth

12
00:00:44,042 --> 00:00:48,042
In the morning, cheese or yogurt with <i>samoon</i> and tea

13
00:00:49,626 --> 00:00:50,834
That was the food they gave

14
00:00:52,417 --> 00:00:53,834
And they gave you water

15
00:00:55,292 --> 00:00:57,292
But it was tap water, not filtered

16
00:00:59,584 --> 00:01:02,918
Interviewer: Was the amount of food enough?

17
00:01:05,667 --> 00:01:07,709
The amount was reasonable

18
00:01:10,876 --> 00:01:15,292
Even if it wasn’t filling

19
00:01:15,876 --> 00:01:17,959
You don’t really feel like eating

20
00:01:19,083 --> 00:01:20,292
Because of the fear and anxiety

21
00:01:22,125 --> 00:01:23,584
You have no appetite to eat

22
00:01:25,542 --> 00:01:28,918
You feel like you’d rather stay hungry for a month

23
00:01:29,334 --> 00:01:31,125
Just to know you’ll get out

24
00:01:34,751 --> 00:01:38,584
Interviewer: During the six days you stayed there

25
00:01:39,792 --> 00:01:44,584
Interviewer: Were the meals given at regular times?
Witness: No

26
00:01:46,459 --> 00:01:51,667
Sometimes they brought dinner with the sunset call to prayer

27
00:01:52,167 --> 00:01:53,959
And sometimes after the night call to prayer

28
00:01:54,334 --> 00:01:57,459
So not tied to time, not at fixed hours

29
00:01:59,792 --> 00:02:01,125
There were no regular times

30
00:02:02,959 --> 00:02:07,751
Interviewer: Were there illnesses in the room?

31
00:02:07,751 --> 00:02:12,959
Were there people with scabies, lice, or diarrhea?

32
00:02:14,209 --> 00:02:16,876
When I arrived

33
00:02:17,709 --> 00:02:23,584
It was still in the beginning

34
00:02:27,209 --> 00:02:29,876
Even electricity was continuous

35
00:02:30,709 --> 00:02:32,667
There were also generators working

36
00:02:33,500 --> 00:02:36,042
When I came in, electricity was available

37
00:02:36,751 --> 00:02:38,709
So there weren’t such cases, I didn’t see that

38
00:02:42,834 --> 00:02:45,000
There were people with mild symptoms

39
00:02:45,042 --> 00:02:48,125
Like a light headache or stomachache

40
00:02:48,626 --> 00:02:50,459
But there wasn’t scabies

41
00:02:50,959 --> 00:02:52,918
The place was clean the first time

42
00:02:53,667 --> 00:02:55,959
But not the second time

43
00:02:57,167 --> 00:02:59,959
You couldn’t tell what was inside because of the dark

44
00:03:01,667 --> 00:03:03,292
It was a basement of a house

45
00:03:05,918 --> 00:03:07,584
You couldn’t tell what it had

46
00:03:08,709 --> 00:03:12,626
You didn’t know if there were snakes, scorpions, or cockroaches

47
00:03:17,834 --> 00:03:20,334
Interviewer: Was there medical care for the prisoners?

48
00:03:20,834 --> 00:03:23,834
Like if you had a headache, would they bring you medicine?

49
00:03:24,500 --> 00:03:27,292
That was in the first time I was imprisoned

50
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:33,250
The first time, they would give you a pill

51
00:03:34,334 --> 00:03:35,626
A pill for inflammation

52
00:03:36,125 --> 00:03:39,042
But the second time they didn’t bring anything

53
00:03:39,542 --> 00:03:43,459
Even if you were close to death, they gave you no medicine

54
00:03:49,083 --> 00:03:51,584
Interviewer: When they brought you a meal and it wasn’t enough

55
00:03:51,626 --> 00:03:52,918
And you wanted to eat more

56
00:03:53,918 --> 00:03:57,667
Could you ask them for another meal?

57
00:03:58,042 --> 00:03:59,459
No, I couldn’t tell them

58
00:04:01,250 --> 00:04:05,792
You couldn’t say to them that you were hungry

59
00:04:07,667 --> 00:04:09,000
You couldn’t ask them for food
